<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1027" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1027">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17036.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Obregon will cross to Juarez tonight and go south early Saturday morning.
                            He informs me that most of the men of Villa and Rodriguez have
                            surrendered but that Villa and Rodriguez have so far escaped plan for
                            their capture.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>